# Copy to .env and edit. NEVER commit the real .env (it's gitignored).
#
# Registration is open to everyone — no invite code or access passphrase.
#
# Optional overrides (sensible defaults already baked into the image):
# PORT=3000
# MAX_BACKUPS_RETAINED=15

# --- OPTIONAL: bot protection (reCAPTCHA v3) ---
# Guards the public auth actions (register/login/recovery) on the WEBSITE against
# bots. Leave RECAPTCHA_SECRET blank to disable verification entirely (open, no
# CAPTCHA — fine for a private/self-hosted server). Get keys (v3) at:
#   https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin
# RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=your_v3_site_key      # public; sent to the browser
# RECAPTCHA_SECRET=your_v3_secret_key      # private; server-side verify
# RECAPTCHA_MIN_SCORE=0.5                  # 0.0–1.0; reject scores below this
#
# APP_API_KEY: the native phone apps can't run reCAPTCHA, so they send this shared
# key as the X-SentryKey-App-Key header to bypass the gate. Must match the value
# baked into the app builds (Android APP_API_KEY gradle prop / iOS Info.plist).
# Generate a strong one, e.g.  openssl rand -base64 24
# APP_API_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-string

# ADMIN_USERS: comma-separated usernames that unlock the admin panel (/admin.html).
# These stay normal zero-knowledge accounts — they log in with their master
# password as usual; being listed here just grants operator access to account
# METADATA (usernames, plans, usage) and plan management. Vault contents are never
# exposed. Example:
# ADMIN_USERS=youradminusername

# --- OPTIONAL: recovery code delivery ---
# Account recovery works WITHOUT any of this (the user's saved recovery key is
# enough). Configure these only to add an email/SMS second factor to recovery.
#
# Email (any SMTP provider — e.g. a free Brevo/SendGrid/Mailgun tier or a Gmail
# app password). Leave blank to disable email codes.
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=apikey-or-username
# SMTP_PASS=your-smtp-password
# SMTP_FROM=SentryKey <noreply@sentrykey.app>
#
# SMS via Twilio (uses the REST API; no SDK needed). Leave blank to disable SMS.
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-twilio-auth-token
# TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=+15551234567
